<!doctype html>
<html>
{{> head }}
<body id="index">
  {{> header }}
  <div class="content">
    <section id="subtitle">
      <h1 class="xl">Offline magic code collaboration.</h1>
      <p>A free and open-source way to host, share, and build software together.</p>
    </section>
    <section id="get-the-app">
      <div id="email-signup">
        <p>Interested in using Radicle?</p>
        <form action="email">
          <input type="text" placeholder="Enter your email"><button>Sign up</button>
        </form>
      </div>
      <img src="/img/org-project-page.png" alt="app image">
    </section>
    <section id="value-prop">
      <h2>Why Radicle?</h2>
      <p>It’s not easy to switch to something new, but here’s why you should.</p>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="value-prop-item">
          {{> svg-p2p }}
          <h2>Peer-to-peer</h2>
          <p>
            No servers. No platforms. No in-betweens. Share your code without relying on a third party.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-prop-item">
          {{> svg-local-first }}
          <h2>Local-first</h2>
          <p>
            All of your issues, revisions, and reviews exist on your computer. You own your data — nobody else.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-prop-item">
          {{> svg-easy-to-use }}
          <h2>Secure</h2>
          <p>
            No need to trust anyone to keep your work safe. With Radicle, everything is signed and backed by public key cryptography.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="get-app">
      <img id="main-illustration" src="/img/garden1.gif" alt="A beautiful garden.">
        <p>Sound interesting?</p>
        <button>Get the app</button>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="tech">
      <h2>The tech behind radicle</h2>
      <p>Radicle is a sovereign stack for code collaboration</p>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="tech-item">
          {{> svg-registry }}
          <h2>registry</h2>
          <p>
            Radicle uses a decentralized identity layer called Registry.
          </p>
          <a href="">Learn more about Registry -></a>
        </div>
        <div class="tech-item">
          {{> svg-link }}
          <h2>link</h2>
          <p>
            For collaboration, Radicle uses Link, a peer-to-peer replication protocol around git.
          </p>
          <a href="">Learn more about link -></a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button>Build your own app</button>
    </section>
  </div>
  {{> footer }}
</body>
</html>
